race.comment: JIMMY MANOLO (3) hasn't won for a long time but has returned in solid order this campaign and is knocking on the door. Backs up quickly and should be hitting his straps now over a favoured trip. Can get the job done. DOUTELLE (6) turned in a fine effort to score by half a length at this track and distance last start to maintain his good form of late. Well placed and there is no reason he cannot repeat the dose. FLAMING MOON (5) is yet to make an impact this time in but should find this easier and is expected to relish the rise in trip. Don't underestimate. LADY TINO (1) strips fitter third-up and can take much closer order from the good draw. Rises quickly in trip on the quick back-up and is among the winning chances.
